Magma to Buy Plutonic, Expand Renewable Energy Capabilities

-- B y   W i l l   W a d e   a n d   M a r i a   E r m a k o v a
-- 
2011-03-07T16:39:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/magma-to-buy-plutonic-for-195-7-million-in-stock-to-expand-renewables.html
  Magma Energy Corp. (MXY) , a Vancouver-
based geothermal power developer, agreed to buy  Plutonic Power
Corp. (PCC)  for C$190 million ($195.7 million) in stock to diversify
its renewable energy capabilities.  Magma, which will change its name to Alterra Power Corp.
after the transaction closes, said in a statement today that
Plutonic investors will receive 2.38 of its shares for every
Plutonic share held.  The valuation is based on the 65.4 million Plutonic shares
outstanding and Magma’s closing price of C$1.22 on March 4. The
price is a 32 percent premium over Plutonic’s 20-day weighted
average, according to the statement. Plutonic also had C$295
million in liabilities at the end of the fourth quarter.  Plutonic operates hydroelectric plants and wind farms, and
announced in January plans to acquire three photovoltaic solar
projects from  First Solar Inc. (FSLR)   The sale must be approved by shareholders of both companies
at meetings to be held in April. The combined company will have
a market capitalization of about C$575 million, according to the
statement.  Magma was down 1 Canadian cent to C$1.21 at 10:12 a.m in
Toronto. Plutonic was up 21 Canadian cents, or 8.7 percent, at
C$2.63.  To contact the reporters on this story:
